<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-17T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-17T01:00:00-05:00" n="680" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115 Pacific War/179: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Nouméa (<persName type="from">MacVitty</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nouméa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-17T17:00:00+11:00">February
                                    17, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received February 17—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>22. The High Commissioner, in connection with the probable defence of New
                            Caledonia by United States forces, requests that he be assured that the
                            American Government recognizes that French sovereignty of the French
                            Pacific possession is exercised by General de Gaulle’s<note n="70" xml:id="d680fn70">Gen. Charles de Gaulle, President of the National
                                Committee of the Free French at London.</note> Comité National
                            Frangais. Also whether an attack by Vichy adherents from Indochina in
                            joint action with the Japanese would be resisted by the American
                            forces.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVitty</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>